5234 
5235 /* Test the public key sign function using the private ket SKEY. PKEY
5236  is used for verification. This variant is only used for ECDSA. */
5237 static void
5238 check_pubkey_sign_ecdsa (int n, gcry_sexp_t skey, gcry_sexp_t pkey)
5239 {
5240  gcry_error_t rc;
5241  gcry_sexp_t sig, badhash, hash;
5242  unsigned int nbits;
5243  int dataidx;
5244  static const struct
5245  {
5246  unsigned int nbits;
5247  const char *data;
5248  int expected_rc;
5249  const char *baddata;
5250  int dummy;
5251  } datas[] =
5252  {
5253  { 192,
5254  "(data (flags raw)\n"
5255  " (value #00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEEFF0001020304050607#))",
5256  0,
5257  "(data (flags raw)\n"
5258  " (value #80112233445566778899AABBCCDDEEFF0001020304050607#))",
5259  0
5260  },
5261  { 256,
5262  "(data (flags raw)\n"
5263  " (value #00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEEFF"
5264  /* */ "000102030405060708090A0B0C0D0E0F#))",
5265  0,
5266  "(data (flags raw)\n"
5267  " (value #80112233445566778899AABBCCDDEEFF"
5268  /* */ "000102030405060708090A0B0C0D0E0F#))",
5269  0
5270  },
5271  { 256,
5272  "(data (flags raw)\n"
5273  " (hash sha256 #00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEEFF"
5274  /* */ "000102030405060708090A0B0C0D0E0F#))",
5275  0,
5276  "(data (flags raw)\n"
5277  " (hash sha256 #80112233445566778899AABBCCDDEEFF"
5278  /* */ "000102030405060708090A0B0C0D0E0F#))",
5279  0
5280  },
5281  { 256,
5282  "(data (flags gost)\n"
5283  " (value #00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEEFF"
5284  /* */ "000102030405060708090A0B0C0D0E0F#))",
5285  0,
5286  "(data (flags gost)\n"
5287  " (value #80112233445566778899AABBCCDDEEFF"
5288  /* */ "000102030405060708090A0B0C0D0E0F#))",
5289  0
5290  },
5291  { 512,
5292  "(data (flags gost)\n"
5293  " (value #00112233445566778899AABBCCDDEEFF"
5294  /* */ "000102030405060708090A0B0C0D0E0F"
5295  /* */ "000102030405060708090A0B0C0D0E0F"
5296  /* */ "000102030405060708090A0B0C0D0E0F#))",
5297  0,
5298  "(data (flags gost)\n"
5299  " (value #80112233445566778899AABBCCDDEEFF"
5300  /* */ "000102030405060708090A0B0C0D0E0F"
5301  /* */ "000102030405060708090A0B0C0D0E0F"
5302  /* */ "000102030405060708090A0B0C0D0E0F#))",
5303  0
5304  },
5305  { 0, NULL }
5306  };
5307 
5308  nbits = gcry_pk_get_nbits (skey);
5309 
5310  for (dataidx = 0; datas[dataidx].data; dataidx++)
5311  {
5312  if (datas[dataidx].nbits != nbits)
5313  continue;
5314 
5315  if (verbose)
5316  fprintf (stderr, " test %d, signature test %d (%u bit ecdsa)\n",
5317  n, dataidx, nbits);
5318 
5319  rc = gcry_sexp_sscan (&hash, NULL, datas[dataidx].data,
5320  strlen (datas[dataidx].data));
5321  if (rc)
5322  die ("converting data failed: %s\n", gpg_strerror (rc));
5323  rc = gcry_sexp_sscan (&badhash, NULL, datas[dataidx].baddata,
5324  strlen (datas[dataidx].baddata));
5325  if (rc)
5326  die ("converting data failed: %s\n", gpg_strerror (rc));
5327 
5328  rc = gcry_pk_sign (&sig, hash, skey);
5329  if (gcry_err_code (rc) != datas[dataidx].expected_rc)
5330  fail ("gcry_pk_sign failed: %s\n", gpg_strerror (rc));
5331 
5332  if (!rc && verbose > 1)
5333  show_sexp ("ECDSA signature:\n", sig);
5334 
5335  if (!rc)
5336  verify_one_signature (pkey, hash, badhash, sig);
5337 
5338  gcry_sexp_release (sig);
5339  sig = NULL;
5340  gcry_sexp_release (badhash);
5341  badhash = NULL;
5342  gcry_sexp_release (hash);
5343  hash = NULL;
5344  }
5345 }
5346 
5347 
5348 static void
5349 check_pubkey_crypt (int n, gcry_sexp_t skey, gcry_sexp_t pkey, int algo)
5350 {
5351  gcry_error_t rc;
5352  gcry_sexp_t plain = NULL;
5353  gcry_sexp_t ciph = NULL;
5354  gcry_sexp_t data = NULL;
5355  int dataidx;
5356  static const struct
5357  {
5358  int algo; /* If not 0 run test only if ALGO matches. */
5359  const char *data;
5360  const char *hint;
5361  int unpadded;
5362  int encrypt_expected_rc;
5363  int decrypt_expected_rc;
5364  int special;
5365  } datas[] =
5366  {
5367  { GCRY_PK_RSA,
5368  "(data\n (flags pkcs1)\n"
5369  " (value #11223344556677889900AA#))\n",
5370  NULL,
5371  0,
5372  0,
5373  0 },
5374  { GCRY_PK_RSA,
5375  "(data\n (flags pkcs1)\n"
5376  " (value #11223344556677889900AA#))\n",
5377  "(flags pkcs1)",
5378  1,
5379  0,
5380  0 },
5381  { GCRY_PK_RSA,
5382  "(data\n (flags oaep)\n"
5383  " (value #11223344556677889900AA#))\n",
5384  "(flags oaep)",
5385  1,
5386  0,
5387  0 },
5388  { GCRY_PK_RSA,
5389  "(data\n (flags oaep)\n (hash-algo sha1)\n"
5390  " (value #11223344556677889900AA#))\n",
5391  "(flags oaep)(hash-algo sha1)",
5392  1,
5393  0,
5394  0 },
5395  { GCRY_PK_RSA,
5396  "(data\n (flags oaep)\n (hash-algo sha1)\n (label \"test\")\n"
5397  " (value #11223344556677889900AA#))\n",
5398  "(flags oaep)(hash-algo sha1)(label \"test\")",
5399  1,
5400  0,
5401  0 },
5402  { GCRY_PK_RSA,
5403  "(data\n (flags oaep)\n (hash-algo sha1)\n (label \"test\")\n"
5404  " (value #11223344556677889900AA#)\n"
5405  " (random-override #4253647587980912233445566778899019283747#))\n",
5406  "(flags oaep)(hash-algo sha1)(label \"test\")",
5407  1,
5408  0,
5409  0 },
5410  { 0,
5411  "(data\n (flags )\n" " (value #11223344556677889900AA#))\n",
5412  NULL,
5413  1,
5414  0,
5415  0 },
5416  { 0,
5417  "(data\n (flags )\n" " (value #0090223344556677889900AA#))\n",
5418  NULL,
5419  1,
5420  0,
5421  0 },
5422  { 0,
5423  "(data\n (flags raw)\n" " (value #11223344556677889900AA#))\n",
5424  NULL,
5425  1,
5426  0,
5427  0 },
5428  { GCRY_PK_RSA,
5429  "(data\n (flags pkcs1)\n"
5430  " (hash sha1 #11223344556677889900AABBCCDDEEFF10203040#))\n",
5431  NULL,
5432  0,
5433  GPG_ERR_CONFLICT,
5434  0},
5435  { 0,
5436  "(data\n (flags raw foo)\n"
5437  " (hash sha1 #11223344556677889900AABBCCDDEEFF10203040#))\n",
5438  NULL,
5439  0,
5440  GPG_ERR_INV_FLAG,
5441  0},
5442  { 0,
5443  "(data\n (flags raw)\n"
5444  " (value #11223344556677889900AA#))\n",
5445  "(flags oaep)",
5446  1,
5447  0,
5448  GPG_ERR_ENCODING_PROBLEM, 1 },
5449  { GCRY_PK_RSA,
5450  "(data\n (flags oaep)\n"
5451  " (value #11223344556677889900AA#))\n",
5452  "(flags pkcs1)",
5453  1,
5454  0,
5455  GPG_ERR_ENCODING_PROBLEM, 1 },
5456  { 0,
5457  "(data\n (flags pss)\n"
5458  " (value #11223344556677889900AA#))\n",
5459  NULL,
5460  0,
5461  GPG_ERR_CONFLICT },
5462  { 0, NULL }
5463  };
5464 
5465  (void)n;
5466 
5467  for (dataidx = 0; datas[dataidx].data; dataidx++)
5468  {
5469  if (datas[dataidx].algo && datas[dataidx].algo != algo)
5470  continue;
5471 
5472  if (verbose)
5473  fprintf (stderr, " encryption/decryption test %d (algo %d)\n",
5474  dataidx, algo);
5475 
5476  rc = gcry_sexp_sscan (&data, NULL, datas[dataidx].data,
5477  strlen (datas[dataidx].data));
5478  if (rc)
5479  die ("converting data failed: %s\n", gpg_strerror (rc));
5480 
5481  rc = gcry_pk_encrypt (&ciph, data, pkey);
5482  if (gcry_err_code (rc) != datas[dataidx].encrypt_expected_rc)
5483  fail ("gcry_pk_encrypt failed: %s\n", gpg_strerror (rc));
5484 
5485  if (!rc)
5486  {
5487  int expect_mismatch = 0;
5488 
5489  /* Insert decoding hint to CIPH. */
5490  if (datas[dataidx].hint)
5491  {
5492  size_t hint_len, len;
5493  char *hint, *buf;
5494  gcry_sexp_t list;
5495 
5496  /* Convert decoding hint into canonical sexp. */
5497  hint_len = gcry_sexp_new (&list, datas[dataidx].hint,
5498  strlen (datas[dataidx].hint), 1);
5499  hint_len = gcry_sexp_sprint (list, GCRYSEXP_FMT_CANON, NULL, 0);
5500  hint = gcry_malloc (hint_len);
5501  if (!hint)
5502  die ("can't allocate memory\n");
5503  hint_len = gcry_sexp_sprint (list, GCRYSEXP_FMT_CANON, hint,
5504  hint_len);
5505  gcry_sexp_release (list);
5506 
5507  /* Convert CIPH into canonical sexp. */
5508  len = gcry_sexp_sprint (ciph, GCRYSEXP_FMT_CANON, NULL, 0);
5509  buf = gcry_malloc (len + hint_len);
5510  if (!buf)
5511  die ("can't allocate memory\n");
5512  len = gcry_sexp_sprint (ciph, GCRYSEXP_FMT_CANON, buf, len);
5513  /* assert (!strcmp (buf, "(7:enc-val", 10)); */
5514 
5515  /* Copy decoding hint into CIPH. */
5516  memmove (buf + 10 + hint_len, buf + 10, len - 10);
5517  memcpy (buf + 10, hint, hint_len);
5518  gcry_free (hint);
5519  gcry_sexp_new (&list, buf, len + hint_len, 1);
5520  gcry_free (buf);
5521  gcry_sexp_release (ciph);
5522  ciph = list;
5523  }
5524  rc = gcry_pk_decrypt (&plain, ciph, skey);
5525  if (!rc && datas[dataidx].special == 1)
5526  {
5527  /* It may happen that OAEP formatted data which is
5528  decrypted as pkcs#1 data returns a valid pkcs#1
5529  frame. However, the returned value will not be
5530  identical - thus we expect a mismatch and test further on
5531  whether this mismatch actually happened. */
5532  expect_mismatch = 1;
5533  }
5534  else if (gcry_err_code (rc) != datas[dataidx].decrypt_expected_rc)
5535  {
5536  if (verbose)
5537  {
5538  show_sexp (" data:\n", data);
5539  show_sexp (" ciph:\n", ciph);
5540  show_sexp (" key:\n", skey);
5541  }
5542  fail ("gcry_pk_decrypt failed: expected %d (%s), got %d (%s)\n",
5543  datas[dataidx].decrypt_expected_rc,
5544  gpg_strerror (datas[dataidx].decrypt_expected_rc),
5545  rc, gpg_strerror (rc));
5546  }
5547 
5548  if (!rc && datas[dataidx].unpadded)
5549  {
5550  gcry_sexp_t p1, p2;
5551 
5552  p1 = gcry_sexp_find_token (data, "value", 0);
5553  p2 = gcry_sexp_find_token (plain, "value", 0);
5554  if (p1 && p2)
5555  {
5556  const char *s1, *s2;
5557  size_t n1, n2;
5558 
5559  s1 = gcry_sexp_nth_data (p1, 1, &n1);
5560  s2 = gcry_sexp_nth_data (p2, 1, &n2);
5561  if (n1 != n2 || memcmp (s1, s2, n1))
5562  {
5563  if (expect_mismatch)
5564  expect_mismatch = 0;
5565  else
5566  fail ("gcry_pk_encrypt/gcry_pk_decrypt "
5567  "do not roundtrip\n");
5568  }
5569  }
5570 
5571  if (expect_mismatch)
5572  fail ("gcry_pk_encrypt/gcry_pk_decrypt "
5573  "expected mismatch did not happen\n");
5574 
5575  gcry_sexp_release (p1);
5576  gcry_sexp_release (p2);
5577  }
5578  }
5579 
5580  gcry_sexp_release (plain);
5581  plain = NULL;
5582  gcry_sexp_release (ciph);
5583  ciph = NULL;
5584  gcry_sexp_release (data);
5585  data = NULL;
5586  }
5587 }
5588 
5589 static void
5590 check_pubkey_grip (int n, const unsigned char *grip,
5591  gcry_sexp_t skey, gcry_sexp_t pkey, int algo)
5592 {
5593  unsigned char sgrip[20], pgrip[20];
5594 
5595  (void)algo;
5596 
5597  if (!gcry_pk_get_keygrip (skey, sgrip))
5598  die ("get keygrip for private RSA key failed\n");
5599  if (!gcry_pk_get_keygrip (pkey, pgrip))
5600  die ("[%i] get keygrip for public RSA key failed\n", n);
5601  if (memcmp (sgrip, pgrip, 20))
5602  fail ("[%i] keygrips don't match\n", n);
5603  if (memcmp (sgrip, grip, 20))
5604  fail ("wrong keygrip for RSA key\n");
5605 }
5606 
5607 static void
5608 do_check_one_pubkey (int n, gcry_sexp_t skey, gcry_sexp_t pkey,
5609  const unsigned char *grip, int algo, int flags)
5610 {
5611  if (flags & FLAG_SIGN)
5612  {
5613  if (algo == GCRY_PK_ECDSA)
5614  check_pubkey_sign_ecdsa (n, skey, pkey);
5615  else
5616  check_pubkey_sign (n, skey, pkey, algo);
5617  }
5618  if (flags & FLAG_CRYPT)
5619  check_pubkey_crypt (n, skey, pkey, algo);
5620  if (grip && (flags & FLAG_GRIP))
5621  check_pubkey_grip (n, grip, skey, pkey, algo);
5622 }
5623 
5624 static void
5625 check_one_pubkey (int n, test_spec_pubkey_t spec)
5626 {
5627  gcry_error_t err = GPG_ERR_NO_ERROR;
5628  gcry_sexp_t skey, pkey;
5629 
5630  err = gcry_sexp_sscan (&skey, NULL, spec.key.secret,
5631  strlen (spec.key.secret));
5632  if (!err)
5633  err = gcry_sexp_sscan (&pkey, NULL, spec.key.public,
5634  strlen (spec.key.public));
5635  if (err)
5636  die ("converting sample key failed: %s\n", gpg_strerror (err));
5637 
5638  do_check_one_pubkey (n, skey, pkey,
5639  (const unsigned char*)spec.key.grip,
5640  spec.id, spec.flags);
5641 
5642  gcry_sexp_release (skey);
5643  gcry_sexp_release (pkey);
5644 }
5645 
5646 static void
5647 get_keys_new (gcry_sexp_t *pkey, gcry_sexp_t *skey)
5648 {
5649  gcry_sexp_t key_spec, key, pub_key, sec_key;
5650  int rc;
5651  if (verbose)
5652  fprintf (stderr, " generating RSA key:");
5653  rc = gcry_sexp_new (&key_spec,
5654  in_fips_mode ? "(genkey (rsa (nbits 4:1024)))"
5655  : "(genkey (rsa (nbits 4:1024)(transient-key)))",
5656  0, 1);
5657  if (rc)
5658  die ("error creating S-expression: %s\n", gpg_strerror (rc));
5659  rc = gcry_pk_genkey (&key, key_spec);
5660  gcry_sexp_release (key_spec);
5661  if (rc)
5662  die ("error generating RSA key: %s\n", gpg_strerror (rc));
5663 
5664  pub_key = gcry_sexp_find_token (key, "public-key", 0);
5665  if (! pub_key)
5666  die ("public part missing in key\n");
5667 
5668  sec_key = gcry_sexp_find_token (key, "private-key", 0);
5669  if (! sec_key)
5670  die ("private part missing in key\n");
5671 
5672  gcry_sexp_release (key);
5673  *pkey = pub_key;
5674  *skey = sec_key;
5675 }
5676 
5677 static void
5678 check_one_pubkey_new (int n)
5679 {
5680  gcry_sexp_t skey, pkey;
5681 
5682  get_keys_new (&pkey, &skey);
5683  do_check_one_pubkey (n, skey, pkey, NULL,
5684  GCRY_PK_RSA, FLAG_SIGN | FLAG_CRYPT);
5685  gcry_sexp_release (pkey);
5686  gcry_sexp_release (skey);
5687 }

5963  int i;
5964 
5965  if (verbose)
5966  fprintf (stderr, "Starting public key checks.\n");
5967  for (i = 0; i < sizeof (pubkeys) / sizeof (*pubkeys); i++)
5968  if (pubkeys[i].id)
5969  {
5970  if (gcry_pk_test_algo (pubkeys[i].id) && in_fips_mode)
5971  {
5972  if (verbose)
5973  fprintf (stderr, " algorithm %d not available in fips mode\n",
5974  pubkeys[i].id);
5975  continue;
5976  }
5977  check_one_pubkey (i, pubkeys[i]);
5978  }
5979  if (verbose)
5980  fprintf (stderr, "Completed public key checks.\n");
5981 
5982  if (verbose)
5983  fprintf (stderr, "Starting additional public key checks.\n");
5984  for (i = 0; i < sizeof (pubkeys) / sizeof (*pubkeys); i++)
5985  if (pubkeys[i].id)
5986  {
5987  if (gcry_pk_test_algo (pubkeys[i].id) && in_fips_mode)
5988  {
5989  if (verbose)
5990  fprintf (stderr, " algorithm %d not available in fips mode\n",
5991  pubkeys[i].id);
5992  continue;
5993  }
5994  check_one_pubkey_new (i);
5995  }
5996  if (verbose)
5997  fprintf (stderr, "Completed additional public key checks.\n");
5998 
5999 }
6000 
6001 int
6002 main (int argc, char **argv)
6003 {
6004  gpg_error_t err;
6005  int last_argc = -1;
6006  int debug = 0;
6007  int use_fips = 0;
6008  int selftest_only = 0;
6009  int pubkey_only = 0;
6010  int loop = 0;
6011  unsigned int loopcount = 0;
6012 
6013  if (argc)
6014  { argc--; argv++; }
6015 
6016  while (argc && last_argc != argc )
6017  {
6018  last_argc = argc;
6019  if (!strcmp (*argv, "--"))
6020  {
6021  argc--; argv++;
6022  break;
6023  }
6024  else if (!strcmp (*argv, "--verbose"))
6025  {
6026  verbose++;
6027  argc--; argv++;
6028  }
6029  else if (!strcmp (*argv, "--debug"))
6030  {
6031  verbose = debug = 1;
6032  argc--; argv++;
6033  }
6034  else if (!strcmp (*argv, "--fips"))
6035  {
6036  use_fips = 1;
6037  argc--; argv++;
6038  }
6039  else if (!strcmp (*argv, "--selftest"))
6040  {
6041  selftest_only = 1;
6042  verbose += 2;
6043  argc--; argv++;
6044  }
6045  else if (!strcmp (*argv, "--pubkey"))
6046  {
6047  pubkey_only = 1;
6048  argc--; argv++;
6049  }
6050  else if (!strcmp (*argv, "--die"))
6051  {
6052  die_on_error = 1;
6053  argc--; argv++;
6054  }
6055  else if (!strcmp (*argv, "--loop"))
6056  {
6057  argc--; argv++;
6058  if (argc)
6059  {
6060  loop = atoi (*argv);
6061  argc--; argv++;
6062  }
6063  }
6064  }
6065 
6066  gcry_control (GCRYCTL_SET_VERBOSITY, (int)verbose);
6067 
6068  if (use_fips)
6069  gcry_control (GCRYCTL_FORCE_FIPS_MODE, 0);
6070 
6071  /* Check that we test exactly our version - including the patchlevel. */
6072  if (strcmp (GCRYPT_VERSION, gcry_check_version (NULL)))
6073  die ("version mismatch; pgm=%s, library=%s\n",
6074  GCRYPT_VERSION,gcry_check_version (NULL));
6075 
6076  if ( gcry_fips_mode_active () )
6077  in_fips_mode = 1;
6078 
6079  if (!in_fips_mode)
6080  gcry_control (GCRYCTL_DISABLE_SECMEM, 0);
6081 
6082  if (verbose)
6083  gcry_set_progress_handler (progress_handler, NULL);
6084 
6085  gcry_control (GCRYCTL_INITIALIZATION_FINISHED, 0);
6086  if (debug)
6087  gcry_control (GCRYCTL_SET_DEBUG_FLAGS, 1u, 0);
6088  /* No valuable keys are create, so we can speed up our RNG. */
6089  gcry_control (GCRYCTL_ENABLE_QUICK_RANDOM, 0);
6090 
6091  do
6092  {
6093  if (pubkey_only)
6094  check_pubkey ();
6095  else if (!selftest_only)
6096  {
6097  check_ciphers ();
6098  check_cipher_modes ();
6099  check_bulk_cipher_modes ();
6100  check_digests ();
6101  check_hmac ();
6102  check_mac ();
6103  check_pubkey ();
6104  }
6105  loopcount++;
6106  if (loop)
6107  {
6108  fprintf (stderr, "Test iteration %u completed.\n", loopcount);
6109  if (loop != -1)
6110  loop--;
6111  }
6112  }
6113  while (loop);
6114 
6115  if (in_fips_mode && !selftest_only)
6116  {
6117  /* If we are in fips mode do some more tests. */
6118  gcry_md_hd_t md;
6119 
6120  /* First trigger a self-test. */
6121  gcry_control (GCRYCTL_FORCE_FIPS_MODE, 0);
6122  if (!gcry_control (GCRYCTL_OPERATIONAL_P, 0))
6123  fail ("not in operational state after self-test\n");
6124 
6125  /* Get us into the error state. */
6126  err = gcry_md_open (&md, GCRY_MD_SHA1, 0);
6127  if (err)
6128  fail ("failed to open SHA-1 hash context: %s\n", gpg_strerror (err));
6129  else
6130  {
6131  err = gcry_md_enable (md, GCRY_MD_SHA256);
6132  if (err)
6133  fail ("failed to add SHA-256 hash context: %s\n",
6134  gpg_strerror (err));
6135  else
6136  {
6137  /* gcry_md_get_algo is only defined for a context with
6138  just one digest algorithm. With our setup it should
6139  put the oibrary intoerror state. */
6140  fputs ("Note: Two lines with error messages follow "
6141  "- this is expected\n", stderr);
6142  gcry_md_get_algo (md);
6143  gcry_md_close (md);
6144  if (gcry_control (GCRYCTL_OPERATIONAL_P, 0))
6145  fail ("expected error state but still in operational state\n");
6146  else
6147  {
6148  /* Now run a self-test and to get back into
6149  operational state. */
6150  gcry_control (GCRYCTL_FORCE_FIPS_MODE, 0);
6151  if (!gcry_control (GCRYCTL_OPERATIONAL_P, 0))
6152  fail ("did not reach operational after error "
6153  "and self-test\n");
6154  }
6155  }
6156  }
6157 
6158  }
6159  else
6160  {
6161  /* If in standard mode, run selftests. */
6162  if (gcry_control (GCRYCTL_SELFTEST, 0))
6163  fail ("running self-test failed\n");
6164  }
6165 
6166  if (verbose)
6167  fprintf (stderr, "\nAll tests completed. Errors: %i\n", error_count);
6168 
6169  if (in_fips_mode && !gcry_fips_mode_active ())
6170  fprintf (stderr, "FIPS mode is not anymore active\n");
6171
